---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Contract-Driven Development — Eidos AGI"
  description="Contracts define what we want. Skills define how to get there. Only one of those survives as AI improves."
>
    <article class="prose-page">
      <header class="page-hero">
        <h1>Contract-Driven<br />Development</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Define what you want. Let the model figure out how.</p>
        <span class="status-badge status-shipped">Shipped</span>
      </header>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>The bitter lesson</h2>
        <p>Richard Sutton's greatest contribution to computer science: general methods that leverage computation always beat hand-crafted human knowledge as compute scales.</p>
        <p>We taught a computer to play chess by giving it the rules (a contract) and a goal (win). We didn't give it opening theory, middlegame strategy, or endgame technique (skills). The system that learned without human strategy knowledge destroyed the one built on decades of human expertise.</p>
        <p>Skills are chess strategy books. Contracts are the rules of chess. One decays with every improvement in reasoning. The other is permanent.</p>

        <!-- Value over time diagram -->
        <div class="cdd-diagram cdd-diagram-wide">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 500 200" fill="none" role="img" aria-label="Contracts hold value as AI improves while skills decay">
            <line x1="60" y1="170" x2="480" y2="170" stroke="var(--color-muted)" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.3"/>
            <line x1="60" y1="170" x2="60" y2="20" stroke="var(--color-muted)" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.3"/>
            <text class="cdd-axis-label" x="270" y="195" text-anchor="middle">AI capability</text>
            <text class="cdd-axis-label" x="15" y="95" text-anchor="middle" transform="rotate(-90 15 95)">value</text>
            <text class="cdd-tick-label" x="120" y="185" text-anchor="middle">GPT-3</text>
            <text class="cdd-tick-label" x="220" y="185" text-anchor="middle">GPT-4</text>
            <text class="cdd-tick-label" x="320" y="185" text-anchor="middle">Opus 4</text>
            <text class="cdd-tick-label" x="420" y="185" text-anchor="middle">AGI</text>
            <path class="cdd-line-contracts" d="M 80 50 Q 200 45 320 40 Q 400 38 460 35"/>
            <text class="cdd-label-contracts" x="465" y="30">contracts</text>
            <path class="cdd-line-skills" d="M 80 55 Q 200 80 280 110 Q 360 140 460 160"/>
            <text class="cdd-label-skills" x="465" y="158">skills</text>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Skills vs contracts</h2>
        <p>The AI ecosystem is building skills — step-by-step instructions that tell models how to accomplish goals. Skills work today. They compensate for what the model can't figure out on its own.</p>
        <p>But skills are written based on today's weaknesses. Go back two years. A skills file for GPT-3 would be extremely verbose. Today's models need less. Tomorrow's need even less. <strong>Skills are technical debt that accrues as models improve.</strong></p>

        <div class="cdd-changes">
          <div>
            <h3>A skill (150 lines)</h3>
            <div class="cdd-code-block">
              <pre><code>Step 1: Read CLAUDE.md
Step 2: Read .visionlog/vision.md
Step 3: Detect project type
Step 4: Score each dimension 1-10
  Use this rubric:
  | Dimension | 1 | 5 | 10 |
  | Reliability | ... | ... |
Step 5: Pick the highest-impact gap
Step 6: Fix it
Step 7: Run tests
Step 8: Record the snapshot</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>A contract (10 lines)</h3>
            <div class="cdd-code-block">
              <pre><code>&#123;
  "goal": "Leave the project better",
  "output": "snapshot.schema.json",
  "constraints": [
    "Every score cites evidence",
    "Fix highest-impact gap",
    "Never violate guardrails",
    "Record every run"
  ]
&#125;</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>The skill tells the model <em>how</em>. The contract tells it <em>what</em>. Models get better at <em>how</em> every six months. <em>What</em> doesn't change.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>A real example</h2>
        <p><a href="https://github.com/eidos-agi/eidos-assistant">Eidos Assistant</a> is a voice notes app with a Mac frontend (Swift), a classification daemon (Python), and a search adapter (Python). Three languages. Three processes. Five JSON Schema contracts hold it together:</p>

        <div class="cdd-contracts-grid">
          <div class="cdd-contract-card">
            <h3>recording-bucket</h3>
            <p>What a voice recording looks like on disk. Audio, transcript, classification — each with defined fields, types, and enums.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cdd-contract-card">
            <h3>daemon-protocol</h3>
            <p>Request/response between the app and the daemon. What gets sent over the socket, what comes back.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cdd-contract-card">
            <h3>adapter-manifest</h3>
            <p>How the app registers itself with the search engine. The app writes it on launch. The search engine reads it. Neither knows about the other's code.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cdd-contract-card">
            <h3>manifest-entry</h3>
            <p>How recordings are tracked for discovery. The app appends entries. The adapter reads them.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cdd-contract-card">
            <h3>performance-metric</h3>
            <p>How transcription speed is tracked. Every recording logs duration, model, and real-time factor.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>Any AI model — current or future — can participate in this system by reading the contracts. The contracts say what data to produce. The model figures out how.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>The confidence model</h2>
        <p>Every fact an agent depends on carries a confidence level. The readiness of a system is the lowest confidence of its parts.</p>
        <table class="cdd-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Level</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Can build on?</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td class="cdd-level cdd-proven">proven</td><td>Tested in production, confirmed working</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="cdd-level cdd-tested">tested</td><td>Validated against real system</td><td>Yes, with monitoring</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="cdd-level cdd-researched">researched</td><td>From documentation, not verified</td><td>Verify first</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="cdd-level cdd-inferred">inferred</td><td>Guessed from similar systems</td><td>No — must verify</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="cdd-level cdd-unknown">unknown</td><td>No information available</td><td>No — must discover</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>The trilogy implements it</h2>
        <div class="cdd-diagram">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 500 80" fill="none" role="img" aria-label="Trilogy pipeline">
            <rect class="cdd-pipe-node" x="10" y="15" width="140" height="50" rx="3"/>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-label" x="80" y="45" text-anchor="middle">research.md</text>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-sub" x="80" y="32" text-anchor="middle">EARN DECISIONS</text>
            <rect class="cdd-pipe-node" x="180" y="15" width="140" height="50" rx="3"/>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-label" x="250" y="45" text-anchor="middle">visionlog</text>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-sub" x="250" y="32" text-anchor="middle">RECORD CONTRACTS</text>
            <rect class="cdd-pipe-node" x="350" y="15" width="140" height="50" rx="3"/>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-label" x="420" y="45" text-anchor="middle">ike.md</text>
            <text class="cdd-pipe-sub" x="420" y="32" text-anchor="middle">EXECUTE</text>
            <line class="cdd-pipe-arrow" x1="150" y1="40" x2="180" y2="40"/>
            <polygon class="cdd-pipe-head" points="174,34 184,40 174,46"/>
            <line class="cdd-pipe-arrow" x1="320" y1="40" x2="350" y2="40"/>
            <polygon class="cdd-pipe-head" points="344,34 354,40 344,46"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="cdd-trio">
          <div class="cdd-trio-item">
            <h3>visionlog</h3>
            <p>Records the contracts — guardrails, goals, ADRs. The constraints all execution must honor.</p>
            <code>pip install visionlog-md</code>
          </div>
          <div class="cdd-trio-item">
            <h3>research.md</h3>
            <p>Earns decisions with evidence. Candidates scored against locked criteria.</p>
            <code>pip install research-md</code>
          </div>
          <div class="cdd-trio-item">
            <h3>ike.md</h3>
            <p>Executes tasks within the contracts. Definition of Done is explicit.</p>
            <code>pip install ike-md</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>The transition</h2>
        <div class="cdd-changes">
          <div>
            <h3>Today</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Define the contract first — the JSON Schema</li>
              <li>Write the skill second — only if the model needs it</li>
              <li>Test without the skill periodically</li>
              <li>Let skills decay — don't maintain them</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Tomorrow</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Contracts are the only artifact</li>
              <li>Models meet contracts without guidance</li>
              <li>Skills directory is empty</li>
              <li>Contracts directory is the entire system</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <p class="cdd-closing">Contracts define what we want, not how to deliver it. That's the primitive that survives AGI.</p>
        <pre><code>pip install visionlog-md research-md ike-md</code></pre>
      </section>

      <div class="related">
        <span class="related-label">Related</span>
        <div class="related-links">
          <a href="/trilogy">The Trilogy</a>
          <a href="/forges">Forges</a>
          <a href="/memory">Memory</a>
          <a href="/eidos">Eidos</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  .cdd-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: var(--text-sm); margin: var(--space-6) 0; }
  .cdd-table th { text-align: left; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3); border-bottom: 2px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 20%, transparent); }
  .cdd-table td { padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3); border-bottom: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 10%, transparent); color: var(--color-muted); }
  .cdd-level { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-weight: var(--weight-medium); }
  .cdd-proven { color: var(--color-command); }
  .cdd-tested { color: var(--color-secondary); }
  .cdd-researched { color: var(--color-primary); }
  .cdd-inferred { color: var(--color-muted); }
  .cdd-unknown { color: var(--color-danger); }
  .cdd-trio { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: var(--space-4); margin-top: var(--space-6); }
  .cdd-trio-item { background: var(--color-surface); padding: var(--space-6); border-radius: var(--radius-md); }
  .cdd-trio-item h3 { color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
  .cdd-trio-item p { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .cdd-trio-item code { font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-command); }
  .cdd-changes { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: var(--space-6); margin-top: var(--space-6); }
  .cdd-changes h3 { font-size: var(--text-base); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .cdd-changes ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .cdd-changes li { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted); padding: var(--space-2) 0; border-bottom: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 8%, transparent); line-height: var(--leading-normal); }
  .cdd-closing { font-size: var(--text-md); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); margin-bottom: var(--space-6); }
  .cdd-diagram { margin: var(--space-8) 0; max-width: 500px; }
  .cdd-diagram-wide { max-width: 540px; }
  .cdd-diagram svg { width: 100%; height: auto; }
  .cdd-code-block { background: var(--color-surface); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--space-4); margin-top: var(--space-3); }
  .cdd-code-block pre { margin: 0; }
  .cdd-code-block code { font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-muted); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); }
  .cdd-contracts-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: var(--space-4); margin: var(--space-6) 0; }
  .cdd-contract-card { background: var(--color-surface); padding: var(--space-5); border-radius: var(--radius-md); }
  .cdd-contract-card h3 { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
  .cdd-contract-card p { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted); line-height: var(--leading-normal); }
  .cdd-axis-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 9px; fill: var(--color-muted); letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
  .cdd-tick-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 8px; fill: var(--color-muted); }
  .cdd-line-contracts { stroke: var(--color-command); stroke-width: 2.5; fill: none; }
  .cdd-label-contracts { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; font-weight: 500; fill: var(--color-command); }
  .cdd-line-skills { stroke: var(--color-danger); stroke-width: 2.5; fill: none; stroke-dasharray: 6 3; }
  .cdd-label-skills { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; font-weight: 500; fill: var(--color-danger); }
  .cdd-pipe-node { fill: var(--color-surface); stroke: var(--color-primary); stroke-width: 1; }
  .cdd-pipe-label { font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 13px; fill: var(--color-text); font-weight: 500; }
  .cdd-pipe-sub { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 7px; fill: var(--color-primary); letter-spacing: 0.1em; }
  .cdd-pipe-arrow { stroke: var(--color-primary); stroke-width: 1.5; stroke-dasharray: 4 3; animation: conf-dash 1.5s linear infinite; }
  .cdd-pipe-head { fill: var(--color-primary); }
  @keyframes conf-dash { to { stroke-dashoffset: -14; } }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .cdd-trio { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .cdd-changes { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .cdd-contracts-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .cdd-table { font-size: var(--text-xs); } }
</style>
